This was their fourth and last album, the only one on a major label (Warner/Reprise). Was produced by Bill Laswell, at Laswell&amp;#039;s Greenpoint Studio in Brooklyn. 

Track listing:
Made to Fire
All My References Are Dead
Love Fed Hate
The Power of Suggestion
Hey Richard
There is No Promise of a Future in the Moment
Hot Bloody Hearts
Suzanne (by Leonard Cohen)
Goodbye Baby
The Devil is Us

Also includes non-Laswell bonus track left off the CD, &quot;If I Were a Girl&quot;, and Bomb midi medley by M. Woody, used in &quot;DIY or DIE&quot; film. 

